==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Consolato del mare
<hw>Con`so*la"to del ma"re</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[It., the
consulate of the sea.]</ety> <def>A collection of maritime laws of
disputed origin, supposed to have been first published at Barcelona
early in the 14th century. It has formed the basis of most of the
subsequent collections of maritime laws.</def> <rj><au>Kent.</au>
<au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Consolator</ent>⟦br⟧
